The paper discusses a framework for high-speed motion planning and control for mobile manipulators, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The learning-based controller and inverse dynamics model also suggest a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments involve ball catching, which could involve computer vision (cs.CV) for object detection and tracking. Finally, the use of optimization algorithms for trajectory generation and control could also relate to systems and control (cs.SY).
